&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Exciting New Opportunity*&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, dynamic and bright individual to work as part of the clinical team to join our continually developing Emergency Departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a key member of the ED team and have an integral role in supporting the management of the ambulance handovers and working collaboratively with the RAT team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is an excellent communicator, a team player, able to multi-task, use their initiative and has a patient led focus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Emergency Departments are extremely busy and the ability to work under pressure is essential. We are looking to employ Nurses, Paramedics or Operating Department Practitioners to join our multi - disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is an excellent opportunity for anyone who wishes to put their current skills to use in a thriving, acute setting with a strong and fast-pace workforce. There will be exciting opportunities to integrate into the nursing team and gain experience in triage &amp; resus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is suited to individuals looking to progress their career within NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
